acuuming work?\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe experiment tried a number of different cleaning methods, swabbing the floors before and after to check for mould and bacteria. Vacuuming was found to be 71% effective overall when it came to cleaning floors.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eThe findings ruled that vacuuming your floors at least once a week was enough to combat mould growth. However, looking at \u003ca data-analytics-id=\"inline-link\" href=\"https://www.idealhome.co.uk/house-manual/cleaning/how-often-should-you-vacuum#section-how-often-should-you-vacuum-hard-floors-vs-carpets\" data-before-rewrite-localise=\"https://www.idealhome.co.uk/house-manual/cleaning/how-often-should-you-vacuum#section-how-often-should-you-vacuum-hard-floors-vs-carpets\"\u003e\u003cu\u003ehow often should you vacuum\u003c/u\u003e\u003c/a\u003e, many experts recommend vacuuming twice a week in general. This is good news - combating mould can easily fit into your normal vacuuming routine, provided you are vacuuming your entire home more than once a week.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003eHowever, Henry admitted he was a little surprised by the results since; ‘ there’s no chemicals at all aiding the cleaning process. That being said, vacuuming is a highly effective method for removing all sorts of dirt, bacteria and allergens that are trapped in carpets, so it’s not altogether surprising that the same’s true for mould.’\u003c/p\u003e\u003cfigure data-bordeaux-image-check=\"\"\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource type=\"image/webp\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-1920-80.jpg.webp 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-1600-80.jpg.webp 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-1280-80.jpg.webp 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-1024-80.jpg.webp 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-768-80.jpg.webp 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-415-80.jpg.webp 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-360-80.jpg.webp 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-320-80.jpg.webp 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\"/\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-320-80.jpg\" alt=\"Shark PowerDetect Clean and Empty Cordless Vacuum testing process\" srcset=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-1920-80.jpg 1920w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-1600-80.jpg 1600w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-1280-80.jpg 1280w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-1024-80.jpg 1024w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-768-80.jpg 768w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-415-80.jpg 415w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-360-80.jpg 360w, https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf-320-80.jpg 320w\" sizes=\"(min-width: 710px) 670px, calc(100vw - 30px)\" loading=\"lazy\" data-original-mos=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf.jpg\" data-pin-media=\"https://cdn.mos.cms.futurecdn.net/hHShu8n6v2Mfo7kJHTSsVf.jpg\"/\u003e\u003c/picture\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003cp\u003e(Image credit: Future/Jullia Joson)\u003c/p\u003e\u003c/figure\u003e\u003cp\u003eAs well as staying up to date with your vacuuming, it’s important to keep on top of your vacuum maintenance too.\u003c/p\u003e\u003cp\u003e‘The best way to prevent dirt and bacteria from building up in your vacuum cleaner is by emptying the container, and cleaning or replacing the filter after each use, depending on the type of vacuum you have,’ says Paul Hambidge, Managing Director at \u003ca data-analytics-id=\"inline-link\" href=\"https://www.factory-direct-flooring.co.uk/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" data-url=\"https://www.factory-direct-flooring